.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Report \- NIP\-56 Reporting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Report;
\&
\&    # Report a profile for spam
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Report\->report(
\&        pubkey      => $my_pubkey,
\&        reported_pk => $spammer_pk,
\&        report_type => \*(Aqspam\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Report a note as illegal
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Report\->report(
\&        pubkey      => $my_pubkey,
\&        reported_pk => $author_pk,
\&        event_id    => $note_id,
\&        report_type => \*(Aqillegal\*(Aq,
\&        content     => \*(AqViolates local law\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Report a blob as malware
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Report\->report(
\&        pubkey      => $my_pubkey,
\&        reported_pk => $author_pk,
\&        report_type => \*(Aqmalware\*(Aq,
\&        blob_hash   => $hash,
\&        event_id    => $containing_event_id,
\&        server      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/file.ext\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse a report event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Report\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->reported_pubkey;
\&    say $info\->report_type;      # nudity, malware, profanity, etc.
\&
\&    # Build a subscription filter
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::Report\->report_filter(
\&        reported_pk => $target_pk,
\&    );
.Ve
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 5
\&    my $report = Net::Nostr::Report\->new(
\&        reported_pubkey => $pubkey_hex,
\&        report_type     => \*(Aqspam\*(Aq,
\&        event_id        => $event_id_hex,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new report object. All fields are optional. Croaks on unknown
arguments. This is the raw constructor; use "report" to build a
complete kind 1984 event.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-56 (Reporting). Provides methods to create kind 1984 report
events, parse existing reports, and build subscription filters.
.PP
Valid report types: \f(CW\*(C`nudity\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`malware\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`profanity\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`illegal\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`spam\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`impersonation\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`other\*(C'\fR.
.SS report
.IX Subsection "report"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Report\->report(
\&        pubkey      => $my_pubkey,
\&        reported_pk => $target_pk,
\&        report_type => \*(Aqspam\*(Aq,
\&        event_id    => $note_id,       # optional, for note reports
\&        blob_hash   => $hash,          # optional, for blob reports
\&        server      => $url,           # optional, for blob reports
\&        content     => \*(Aqreason\*(Aq,       # optional
\&        labels      => [               # optional, NIP\-32
\&            [\*(AqL\*(Aq, \*(Aqnamespace\*(Aq],
\&            [\*(Aql\*(Aq, \*(Aqvalue\*(Aq, \*(Aqnamespace\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1984 report event. For profile\-only reports, the report type
is placed on the \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag. For note reports (\f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR provided), the type
is placed on the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag. For blob reports (\f(CW\*(C`blob_hash\*(C'\fR provided), the
type is placed on the \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR tag and \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR is required.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 6
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Report\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->reported_pubkey;
\&    say $info\->report_type;
\&    say $info\->event_id;    # undef for profile\-only reports
\&    say $info\->blob_hash;   # undef unless blob report
\&    say $info\->server;      # undef unless provided
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 1984 report event and returns a Net::Nostr::Report object.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Report\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a kind 1984 report event. Croaks if the event is not kind 1984,
has no \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag, or has an \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR tag without a corresponding \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS report_filter
.IX Subsection "report_filter"
.Vb 5
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::Report\->report_filter(
\&        reported_pk => $target_pk,
\&        event_id    => $note_id,
\&        authors     => [$reporter_pk],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns a subscription filter hashref for querying report events. All
parameters are optional.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS reported_pubkey
.IX Subsection "reported_pubkey"
Hex pubkey of the reported user.
.SS report_type
.IX Subsection "report_type"
Report type string: \f(CW\*(C`nudity\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`malware\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`profanity\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`illegal\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`spam\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`impersonation\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`other\*(C'\fR.
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
Reported event ID (64\-char lowercase hex), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for profile\-only
reports.
.SS blob_hash
.IX Subsection "blob_hash"
Blob SHA\-256 hash, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS server
.IX Subsection "server"
Server URL for blob reports, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-56 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/56.md>,
Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Event
